<reggrp_short_dscr>:
QoS mapping table
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
The QoS mapping table MAP_TBL is looked up twice per frame with the keys defined by default QoS mapping (ANA_CL:PORT:MAP_CFG) or VCAP_CLM actions. 

SET_CTRL defines which values are returned from the QoS mapping table. The actual values are programmed in MAP_ENTRY. 

The QoS mapping table is laid out with 8 entries per row. MAP_IDX points to a row in the table. Depending on the key used to look up the table, one or more rows counting from the MAP_IDX are used by the mapping. For each row used, SET_CTRL must be configured.
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Configures which entry fields to use if row is matched
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
If set, TC_VAL replaces the classified TC bits if the entry is matched.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
If set, DP_VAL replaces the classified DP level if the entry is matched.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
If set, QOS_VAL replaces the classified QoS class if the entry is matched.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
If set, DEI_VAL replaces the classified DEI value if the entry is matched.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
If set, PCP_VAL replaces the classified PCP value if the entry is matched.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
If set, DSCP_VAL replaces the classified DSCP value if the entry is matched.
