<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Router Leg Table
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
A router leg is identified by a 9 bit wide "VMID".

The parameters in this table are used only for frames received by ANA_CL from VD2, i.e. IP-in-IP frames which have been encapsulated or decapsulated.
Such frames have no Ethernet layer and no ingress port. Instead they are always IP frames and have an ingress VMID, which is used to lookup parameters in ANA_CL:VMID.
The ingress VMID for frames forwarded through VD2 is configured in REW, see parameters below.

For frames arriving on an Ethernet port, the ingress VMID will normally be determined by ANA_L3 and the parameters in ANA_CL:VMID will not apply.

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:VMID
REW:ENCAP_IP4:IRLEG_CFG.IRLEG
REW:VMID:RLEG_CTRL.DECAP_IRLEG
